window.bookSummaryJSON = "Thirty-four years ago, Violet Sullivan put on her party finery and left for the annual Fourth of July fireworks display. She was never seen again. <p> In the small California town of Serena Station, tongues wagged. Some said she'd run off with a lover. Some said she was murdered by her husband.</p> <p> But for the not-quite-seven-year-old daughter Daisy she left behind, Violet's absence has never been explained or forgotten.</p> <p> Now, 34 years later, she wants the solace of closure.</p>"; 
